products.title: Kite, Cloud - Roller Blind
products.description: When you take a look at the quaint and homely pattern of kite cloud, you get that feeling of being ready to put your feet up and get comfy. The playful shapes scatter themselves across the fabric, whilst the light grey background instantly sets your mind at ease. We love the idea of pairing cloud with a light laminate floor and some cream leather couches. That way you can introduce plenty of light colour contrasts in the living room without having to reach for your paintbrushes.

products.title: Mulberry, Neutral - Roller Blind
products.description: Mulberry neutral gives you a starting point from which you can set the tone for your new decor. The relaxed and homely aesthetic is perfect when you want to add that warm and cosy feeling to any space your heart desires. Adding homely touches like slate coasters, logs by the fire, and jars of warm white fairy lights is a great direction to go in. Adding things just because you love the way they look is the name of the game here.

products.title: Romance, Breeze - Roller Blind
products.description: Pastel blues and indigo-greys are the stars of the show in the floral, ultra-pretty romance breeze, a durable yet lightweight blind that allows just enough light to filter through, whilst still offering privacy and shade. Set the breeze against cool blue bedroom walls and bring out the indigo with occasional furnishings and accessories. Or instead, give your utility or hallway a delicate pop of colour to add interest to magnolia or cream walls.

products.title: Florence, Coral - Roller Blind
products.description: The beauty of florence coral is that it allows you to see something subtly different every time you look at it. There are so many different shades of green and pink working together, that you really get the feel that the fabric has a life and soul all of its own. When you want to work coral into your decor, you need to be bold with your use of shape and form. Striking country artwork that immediately catches the eye, and a rug in front of the log burner would make for welcome additions.

products.title: Romance, Haze - Roller Blind
products.description: Olive greens and berry purples make up the floral pattern of the romance haze, which is a classic yet contemporary light-filtering blind. The lightweight fabric is moved up and down to your liking by an easy-to-use roller mechanism, and is durable and long-lasting in quality. The haze will sit pretty in any romantic, country bedroom, and is best complemented by creams and lilacs. Alternatively, sit against olive green, shaker-style units in a kitchen, where it will work with both rustic dcor and modern appliances.

products.title: Kite, Sunburst - Roller Blind
products.description: Kite sunburst is one of those playful patterns that adds a homely touch to your space, no matter where you decide to use it. The triangles scatter across the sunny fabric, and give it a relaxed vibe that can be rather hard to find with patterned designs. For a look you'll love the moment you walk in the door, contrast sunburst against some soft aqua blue walls and a white rug. That way you can introduce natural calming shades and hues into the bedroom, and fall asleep the moment your head hits the pillow.

products.title: Watercolour, Mango - Roller Blind
products.description: As you stand back and admire watercolour mango, you come to appreciate the artisan skill that goes into created such a design. The fabric is dominated by subtle variations of blacks, greys, and whites, and yet it's the splash of mango that stands out from across the room. When you want to be able to introduce something a little different into your home, the upstairs landing is often the place to do it.

products.title: Florence, Mustard - Roller Blind
products.description: Florence mustard gets its name from the tangy yellow that sits in the background, but this is a design that offers far more than that. The artistic nature of the florals gives the fabric a beautiful sketched quality that instantly captures the imagination. Imagine all of the new creative avenues this opens up for your next home interiors project. If you want to be able to start the day with a smile, use mustard in the bedroom.

products.title: Watercolour, Gold - Roller Blind
products.description: When you're looking for a contemporary design that will fill any space, watercolour gold could be just what you need. The subtle way in which the greys ebb and flow into one another is accentuated by the gentle dash of gold that instantly catches your eye. If you're looking for a way to add a focal point to the guest bedroom, gold holds all the answers. By turning your window spaces into a piece of modern art, you can solve the old problem of deciding on a style that a dozen different guests will love.

products.title: Summer Trail, Blossom - Roller Blind
products.description: Summer trail blossom is the finishing touch to one of their most popular ranges, and the selection of country chic colours are the reason we consider it one of their jewels in the crown. There are so many exciting creative avenues that open up to you that it'll be hard to know which one to explore first. Crisp blues and light mint greens will work in perfect harmony with blossom to create a look that will live long in the memory.

products.title: Springtime, Beam - Roller Blind
products.description: Springtime brings plenty of opportunities for growth and renewal, and with beam you get to experience the vibrancy of colour first hand. Lush greens and energetic yellows give you a window into a world of design where anything is possible. Just what you need when you want to be able to create a space that always sets you at ease. A light blue and a pink power red are great colours to work into the master bedroom if you want a light and vibrant room that greets you with a smile every morning.

products.title: Romance, Mustard - Roller Blind
products.description: Romance in mustard is a leafy, floral blind that allows daylight to gently filter through. The high quality fabric is grainy to the touch, giving it a beautifully country-like feel, and the yellow and grey-green shades fit together perfectly. Hang the mustard in your bedroom against accented olive green walls and pretty cream furnishings for a classy, outdoorsy look. Or, for a country style kitchen, add in terracotta reds and muted sky blues to create a cosy, lived in atmosphere.

products.title: Odette, Cherry - Roller Blind
products.description: The odette in cherry offers a timeless style and a deep, sophisticated colour scheme that will fit most dcor schemes, whether traditional or contemporary. The canvas-like fabric is sturdy and hardwearing, with a high quality finish, and allows just a touch of light to filter through when it's closed. Complement deep reds and burgundy shades by hanging the cherry in the kitchen amongst dark woods and white units, for a classic look that simply won't age.

products.title: Etching, Primrose - Roller Blind
products.description: Etching primrose combines a nuanced look with some life-affirming colours to create a visual that you'll instantly fall in love with. The beauty of it lies in the simplicity, and it's a look we know you'll cherish the moment it lands on your doorstep. If you want to breathe new life into the guest bedroom there's no better way to do it than with a striking fabric that instantly adds something unexpected.

products.title: Herringbone, Black - Roller Blind
products.description: Sometimes all a great interior needs is simplicity. When you want to be able to bring your space to life, the minimalist stylings of herringbone enable you to do exactly that, whilst simultaneously adding a modern twist. The gentle off-white background works in perfect harmony with the definitive black lines to create a look to cherish. If you want to add some geometric patterning to your interior, the secret is not to overdo things.

products.title: Verdi (Blackout), Silk White - Roller Blind
products.description: The beauty of verdi (blackout) silk white is the way in which it sits there ever so luxurious, and yet it remains neutral at the same time. It's a hard balance to strike, but when you see it you'll wonder why you never thought of it before. Taking your decor in a luxury direction is what we all dream of, so why wait any longer? A black leather couch and a large rug under the coffee table would be ideal ways to take the living room where you want to go.

products.title: Verdi (Blackout), Kiwi Breeze - Roller Blind
products.description: When you want to discover shades that warm the heart and breathe new life into your home you need to look to the natural world for inspiration. Kiwi breeze is the verdi (blackout) range's latest addition, and the zesty green is sure to catch the eye for all the right reasons. Taking your time is what all great interior design projects require, so spend some time searching for a pattern that can compliment the intricate stitching of kiwi breeze.

products.title: Verdi (Blackout), Dusty Plum - Roller Blind
products.description: Take a closer look at verdi (blackout) dusty plum and you'll soon see why it's a fabric that's proving to be a hit with all different styles of modern decor. The deep and moody purple is perfectly tempered by the intricate ornate patterning that shimmers gently in the light. Just what you need when having your home look its best is the only option. Pairing the deep tones of dusty plum with a zesty green or a powdered orange would be an inspired way to work in more natural shades.

products.title: Luster, Storm - Roller Blind
products.description: As you take in the moody quality of luster storm you instantly get a feel for how it got its name. The stone grey has a timeless look that makes you feel like it has a thousand and one different stories to tell. Just what you need when you want to add some character to the modern home. Sandy beiges, creams, and pine are all great bedfellows for storm. They balance out the dark tones by introducing lighter surfaces that still have plenty of character and individuality.

products.title: Luster, Grey - Roller Blind
products.description: The beauty of luster grey is the way in which it breaks up the traditional single colour fabrics with dashes of white. It gives the whole blind a larger than life quality that lets the light flow around your room without saturating the existing colours. Introducing other finely detailed finishes would be an inspired choice if you want to continue the theme around the room. Look to the natural world for inspiration by focusing on the huge variety of wood grains that you can introduce with your furniture and flooring.
